Filgotinib (GLPG0634) is a selective JAK1 inhibitor with IC50 of 10 nM; 28 nM; 810 nM; and 116 nM for JAK1; JAK2; JAK3; and TYK2; respectively. Phase 2.
SMI-4a is a potent inhibitor of Pim1 with IC50 of 17 nM; modest potent to Pim-2; does not significantly inhibit other serine/threonine- or tyrosine-kinases.
AZD5363 potently inhibits all isoforms of Akt(Akt1/Akt2/Akt3) with IC50 of 3 nM/8 nM/8 nM; similar to P70S6K/PKA and lower activity towards ROCK1/2. Phase 1/2.
WY 14643 (Pirinixic Acid) is a potent peroxisome proliferator and activator of PPAR_ with EC50 of 1.5 _M.
PU-H71 is a potent and selective inhibitor of HSP90 with IC50 of 51 nM. Phase 1.
ETP-46464 is a potent and selective inhibitor of ATR with IC50 of 25 nM.
AZD3463 is a novel orally bioavailable ALK inhibitor with Ki of 0.75 nM; which also inhibits IGF1R with equivalent potency.
CO-1686 is an irreversible; mutant-selective EGFR inhibitor with Ki of 21.5 nM and 303.3 nM for EGFRL858R/T790M and EGFRWT; respectively. Phase 1/2.
XL888 is an ATP-competitive inhibitor of HSP90 with IC50 of 24 nM.
PJ34 HCl is the hydrochloride salt of PJ34; which is a PARP inhibitor with EC50 of 20 nM and is equally potent to PARP1/2.
P22077 is an inhibitor of ubiquitin-specific protease USP7 with EC50 of 8.6 _M; also inhibits the closely related USP47.
EHop-016 is a specific Rac GTPase inhibitor with IC50 of 1.1 _M for Rac1; equally potent inhibition for Rac3.
LGK-974 is a potent and specific PORCN inhibitor; and inhibits Wnt signaling with IC50 of 0.4 nM. Phase 1.
K-Ras(G12C) inhibitor 9 is an allosteric inhibitor of oncogenic K-Ras(G12C).
Batimastat (BB-94) is a potent; broad spectrum matrix metalloprotease (MMP) inhibitor for MMP-1; MMP-2; MMP-9; MMP-7 and MMP-3 with IC50 of 3 nM; 4 nM; 4 nM; 6 nM and 20 nM; respectively.
EPZ004777 is a potent; selective DOT1L inhibitor with IC50 of 0.4 nM.
SKI II is a highly selective and non ATP-competitive S1P receptor inhibitor with IC50 of 0.5 _M; while exhibits no inhibitory on other kinases including PI3K; PKC_ and ERK2.
GNE-0877 is a highly potent and selective leucine-rich repeat kinase 2 (LRRK2) inhibitor with Ki of 0.7 nM.
BIO (6-bromoindirubin-3'-oxime) is a specific inhibitor of GSK-3 with IC50 of 5 nM for GSK-3_/_; shows >16-fold selectivity over CDK5; also a pan-JAK inhibitor.
Leupeptin Hemisulfate is a reversible inhibitor of serine and cysteine proteases.
Losmapimod (GW856553X) is a selective; potent; and orally active p38 MAPK inhibitor with pKi of 8.1 and 7.6 for p38_ and p38_; respectively. Phase 3.
Caffeic acid phenethyl ester is a potent and specific inhibitor of NF-_B activation; and also displays antioxidant; immunomodulatory and antiinflammatory activities.
OG-L002 is a potent and specific LSD1 inhibitor with IC50 of 20 nM; exhibiting 36- and 69-fold selectivity over MAO-B and MAO-A; respectively.
TAPI-1 is an ADAM17/TACE inhibitor; which blocks shedding of cytokine receptors.
NMS-P937 (NMS1286937) is an orally available; selective Polo-like Kinase 1 (PLK1) inhibitor with IC50 of 2 nM; 5000-fold selectivity over PLK2/PLK3. Phase 1.
CRT0044876 is a potent and selective APE1 inhibitor with IC50 of ~3 _M.
WIKI4 is a novel Tankyrase inhibitor with IC50 of 15 nM for TNKS2; and leads to inhibition of Wnt/beta-catenin signaling.
JNK inhibitor IX is a selective and potent JNK inhibitor with pIC50 of 6.5 and 6.7 for JNK2 and JNK3; respectively.
GS-9973 is an orally bioavailable; selective Syk inhibitor with IC50 of 7.7 nM. Phase 2.
Pritelivir (BAY 57-1293) is a potent helicase primase inhibitor; exhibiting antiviral effect on herpes simplex virus (HSV) with IC50 of 20 nM for both HSV-1 and HSV-2.
Lomitapide is a potent microsomal triglyceride transfer protein (MTP) inhibitor; used in the treatment of familial hypercholesterolemia.

BIX01294 is an inhibitor of G9a histone methyltransferase with IC50 of 2.7 _M; reduces H3K9me2 of bulk histones; also weakly inhibits GLP (primarily H3K9me3); no significant activity observed at other histone methyltransferases.
GW0742 is a potent and highly selective PPAR_/_ agonist; with IC50 of 1 nM; with 1000-fold selectivity over hPPAR_ and hPPAR_.
NSC 23766 is an inhibitor of Rac GTPase targeting Rac activation by guanine nucleotide exchange factors (GEFs) with IC50 of ~50 _M; does not inhibit the closely related  targets; Cdc42 or RhoA.
GDC-0349 is a potent and selective ATP-competitive inhibitor of mTOR with Ki of 3.8 nM; 790-fold inhibitory effect against PI3K_ and other 266 kinases. Phase 1.
Macitentana (Actelion-1; ACT-064992) is an orally active; non-peptide; dual ETA/ETB (endothelin) receptor antagonist with IC50 of 0.5 nM/391 nM. Phase 3.
